linuxMIB.description: Experimental MIB modules for the linux operating system.

LoadValue.name: LoadValue
LoadValue.description: This data type represents a systems load average over a given time interval. Every usage of this textual convention is required to specify the time interval. A value represents the average number of processes ready to run times 100.

linuxCPU.name: linuxCPU
linuxCPU.description: The identification of the linux CPUs. This string contains foreach CPU present in the system the CPU type, model and vendor (if known by the operating system).

linuxBogo.name: linuxBogo
linuxBogo.description: The number of BOGO MIPS of the linux system.

linuxLoadAvg1.name: linuxLoadAvg1
linuxLoadAvg1.description: The average system load during the last 60 seconds.

linuxLoadAvg5.name: linuxLoadAvg5
linuxLoadAvg5.description: The average system load during the last 5 minutes.

linuxLoadAvg15.name: linuxLoadAvg15
linuxLoadAvg15.description: The average system load during the last 15 minutes.

linuxCompliance.name: linuxCompliance
linuxCompliance.description: The compliance statement for an SNMP entity which implements the linux MIB.

linuxGroup.name: linuxGroup
linuxGroup.description: A collection of linux specific objects.
